For each issue:
1. Read the issue description to understand what needs to change.
2. Make the fix with a fixup commit targeting the relevant SHA:
   git commit --fixup=<sha>
3. Run relevant tests.
4. Close the issue: bd close <issue-id>

After creating a fixup commit, check whether your changes affect code that
later commits also touch:
1. Run git log --oneline <target-sha>..HEAD to list downstream commits.
2. If your fixup renamed an identifier, changed a function signature,
   modified an interface, or altered a type that later commits reference,
   create additional fixup commits for each affected downstream commit.
3. Each additional fixup must target the correct downstream SHA:
   git commit --fixup=<downstream-sha>

Rules:
- Fix all listed issues. Do not implement new steps.
